theorem Topology.interior_inter_frontier_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior (A : Set X) ∩ frontier A = (∅ : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- The interior of `A` is disjoint from the frontier of `A`.
  have hDisjoint : Disjoint (interior (A : Set X)) (frontier A) := by
    -- `frontier A` is `closure A \ interior A`.
    simpa [frontier] using
      (Topology.disjoint_interior_boundary (A := A))
  -- Translate disjointness into the intersection being empty.
  apply (Set.eq_empty_iff_forall_not_mem).2
  intro x hx
  have : False := (Set.disjoint_left).1 hDisjoint hx.1 hx.2
  exact this.elim

theorem Topology.frontier_inter_subset_inter_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    frontier (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ closure A ∩ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  -- `hx` gives that `x` is in the closure of `A ∩ B`.
  have h_cl : x ∈ closure (A ∩ B : Set X) := hx.1
  -- The closure of an intersection is contained in the intersection
  -- of the closures.
  have h_subset : closure (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ closure A ∩ closure B :=
    Topology.closure_inter_subset (A := A) (B := B)
  -- Combining the two facts yields the desired membership.
  exact h_subset h_cl
